XPaXS requires several packages in order to run:

* numpy (version 1.1 or later, please install from svn for now)
* python (version 2.5 or later)
* Qt4 (preferrably version 4.3.3 or later)
* PyQt4 (preferrably version 4.3.3 or later)
* matplotlib (0.92.1 or later, please install from svn for now)
* PyMca (version 4.2.4 or later)
* pexpect (only required for the console module)
* pp (parallel python for concurrent data analysis)
* pytables (version 2.0.3 or later)

On several distributions, like Ubuntu, you may need to install the developer
tools and devel libraries in order to use XPaXS.


In order to compile the documentation, you will also need:

* sphinx (please install from svn for now)

